imdb.plot outline: It's been said that "well-behaved women seldom make history", but the handful of white boys who wrote our History books conveniently left out most of them out. Whoops! To rectify this situation, sisters Hannah and Eliza are setting out to unearth the forgotten stories of the badass sheilas of Australian History. The series transforms these women's stories into a hilarious blend of information and entertainment that inspires young people with tales of the pioneering, tough-titted ladies who hiked up their petticoats and fly-kicked down the doors of opportunity for modern Australia.
